cff-version: 1.2.0
title: Hillstar - Security and Reproducibility-First Workflow Orchestrator
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata from this file.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Gamboa
    given-names: Julen
repository-code: 'https://github.com/jgamboa/hillstar-orchestrator'
url: 'https://github.com/jgamboa/hillstar-orchestrator'
abstract: >-
  Hillstar is an open-source workflow orchestrator built for scientific research
  labs and regulated environments where reproducibility and auditability are
  non-negotiable. Designed with security and governance as first-class concerns,
  Hillstar enables explicit, auditable coordination between multiple LLM
  providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Mistral, Ollama) and external agents via MCP
  servers. Every decision is logged: which model was called, what parameters
  were used, how much it cost, and whether review was required. Built for
  research environments handling sensitive data—genomic studies, clinical trials,
  proprietary research—where governance is the foundation, not an afterthought.
keywords:
  - LLM orchestration
  - workflow management
  - multi-provider coordination
  - reproducibility
  - auditability
  - research automation
  - governance
  - security
